    "explanation": "<p>We know that following are the cases when a compound is optically inactive:</p>\n<p>1. When it does not have a chiral carbon atom e.g., Methyl bromide</p>\n<p>2. When it has a plane or axis of symmetry e.g., Tartaric acid (these compounds are called as Meso compounds)</p>\n<p>3. When it forms a racemic mixture e.g.: Equimolar mixture of d-Lactic acid and l-Lactic acid.</p>\n<p>The given compound possesses an axis of symmetry</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lg94r1z1/210adddc-5648-4cde-b0b4-6f10ad06bc43/b6c0b6d0-d6ae-11ed-89f6-65b3651d9edd/file-1lg94r1z2.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lg94r1z1/210adddc-5648-4cde-b0b4-6f10ad06bc43/b6c0b6d0-d6ae-11ed-89f6-65b3651d9edd/file-1lg94r1z2.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 60vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2008 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 5 English Explanation\"></p>",
