    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>KI in acetone, undergoes S<sub>N</sub>2 reaction with each of P, Q, R and S. The rates of the reaction vary as</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l1sah9ln/7acb6a63-1042-41fb-859d-61e1ab0f8c5f/c2fbeab0-b840-11ec-a05a-a710251ca16c/file-1l1sah9lo.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l1sah9ln/7acb6a63-1042-41fb-859d-61e1ab0f8c5f/c2fbeab0-b840-11ec-a05a-a710251ca16c/file-1l1sah9lo.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2013 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 7 English\"></p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "P > Q > R > S"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "S > P > R > Q"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "P > R > Q > S"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "R > P > S > Q"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p> The bulky groups cause steric hindrance in the formation of transition state. Therefore, higher homologues (Q) are less reactive than lower homologues (P). In compound (S), the transition state is highly stabilized by Ph-(C=O)- group, so it has highest rate of reaction towards S<sub>N</sub>2. </p>\n<p>The relative reactivities towards S<sub>N</sub>2 reaction S > P > R > Q.</p>",
    "topic": "haloalkanes",
    "year": 2013,
    "yearKey": "jee-advanced-2013-paper-1-offline",
    "difficulty": "medium"
  },
  {
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The major product of the following reaction is:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lg870gif/a7dc522f-c59f-4d96-a64f-17cba805f2ca/c5dfea70-d62a-11ed-8aa5-3d8518058bec/file-1lg870gig.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lg870gif/a7dc522f-c59f-4d96-a64f-17cba805f2ca/c5dfea70-d62a-11ed-8aa5-3d8518058bec/file-1lg870gig.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2008 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 6 English\"></p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lg870zhs/17c493ac-465a-4815-bfbe-b4506f3e548f/d48993f0-d62a-11ed-a810-4d71dabfb4ba/file-1lg870zht.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lg870zhs/17c493ac-465a-4815-bfbe-b4506f3e548f/d48993f0-d62a-11ed-a810-4d71dabfb4ba/file-1lg870zht.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2008 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 6 English Option 1\">"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lg871nvl/b8a30a49-26e9-41b4-b00f-c8173840f302/e75fa910-d62a-11ed-a810-4d71dabfb4ba/file-1lg871nvm.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lg871nvl/b8a30a49-26e9-41b4-b00f-c8173840f302/e75fa910-d62a-11ed-a810-4d71dabfb4ba/file-1lg871nvm.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2008 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 6 English Option 2\">"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lg872a2r/b2476fd3-733b-4269-a3e8-d0ba110e7728/f8859d30-d62a-11ed-a810-4d71dabfb4ba/file-1lg872a2s.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lg872a2r/b2476fd3-733b-4269-a3e8-d0ba110e7728/f8859d30-d62a-11ed-a810-4d71dabfb4ba/file-1lg872a2s.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2008 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 6 English Option 3\">"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lg872tf1/cf36844c-9074-4b5a-90fc-db98b4390f7e/077661d0-d62b-11ed-a810-4d71dabfb4ba/file-1lg872tf2.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lg872tf1/cf36844c-9074-4b5a-90fc-db98b4390f7e/077661d0-d62b-11ed-a810-4d71dabfb4ba/file-1lg872tf2.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2008 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 6 English Option 4\">"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Alkyl halides undergo nucleophilic substitution more readily than aryl halides due to partial double bond character between aryl carbon and halogen. Hence, substitution occurs more readily in the side chain rather than in the ring. PhS$$^-$$ is a strong nucleophile and dimethylformamide (DMF) is a highly polar aprotic solvent. Hence, nucleophilic substitution (S$$_\\mathrm{N}2$$) takes place at 2$$^\\circ$$ benzylic carbon. Stereochemically, it involves inversion of configuration at benzylic carbon atom.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lg87c96w/4d30c3ab-e61f-4d6d-a00f-ae9d22605c46/0dee0080-d62c-11ed-a810-4d71dabfb4ba/file-1lg87c96x.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lg87c96w/4d30c3ab-e61f-4d6d-a00f-ae9d22605c46/0dee0080-d62c-11ed-a810-4d71dabfb4ba/file-1lg87c96x.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2008 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 6 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Alkyl group exhibit neighbouring group participation or anchimeric assistance from aryl group but deactivation by $$-$$NO$$_2$$ and $$-$$F makes S$$_\\mathrm{N}1$$ difficult and retention of configuration at chiral carbon does not takes place.</p>",
    "topic": "haloarenes",
    "year": 2008,
    "yearKey": "iit-jee-2008-paper-1-offline",
    "difficulty": "medium"
  },
